          <h2 class="node-title"><a href="b/xampp-apache-vhosts-ssl.html">XAMPP: Apache Vhosts with SSL</a></h2>
    
          <div class="meta">Submitted by tomo on July 18, 2011 - 6:21pm</div>
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_6 first"><a href="category/type/tech.html" rel="tag" title="">Tech</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_56"><a href="category/tags/apache.html" rel="tag" title="">apache</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_128"><a href="category/tags/https.html" rel="tag" title="">https</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_127"><a href="category/tags/ssl.html" rel="tag" title="">ssl</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_129"><a href="category/tags/vhosts.html" rel="tag" title="">vhosts</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_130 last"><a href="category/tags/xampp.html" rel="tag" title="">xampp</a></li>
</ul></div>
    
  </div> <!-- /.node-header -->

  <div class="content">
    
    <p>I needed to test out ssl on my Macbook as a web server with XAMPP. &nbsp;It took more effort than it should have because I was using virtual hosts as well.</p>

<a href="b/xampp-apache-vhosts-ssl.html">Read the rest of this article...</a>  </div>

